Beau yé Roc

▶︎ latest release

  • international black labor strike

    "international black labor strike" is the B side to "new afrika, 21'", a project that was created in response to the bitter truths about exploitation, one's worth, one's expectations, and being black within a racial-capitalist nation. Recorded through the end of September 2021 into the beginning of that October, the work was a manifestation of escapism through creation and a subconscious outpouring of questions linked to the times.

▶︎ discography

  • new afrika, '21

    "new afrika, '21" was created within 2 weeks amidst unemployment during the covid-19 pandemic. My political leanings were different and the excitement I once felt about participating in the world as it was had fled. This tape was a fleeting opportunity to escape from financial insecurity and the withering of my self esteem, to settle momentarily in a practice I had exercised since 2013.

  • staff picks (new world anthology)

    "staff picks (new world anthology)" was arranged from beats and loops left over some years and months on USBs and hard drives. The "staff" was in reference to myself. "new world anthology" was in reference to the possibilities lying ahead through the seizing of our destinies, the power in our intent.

  • world literature for mutual aid*

    "world literature for mutual aid" was initially released as an EP to help fund resources during the winter storm of February 2021. Since then, the project has been updated with several more tracks and will continue to be updated as an ever-growing body of music.

  • new world series

    "new world series" was an EP following the release of "world art, pt. i".

  • world art, pt. i

    "world art, pt. i" was an album mixed from a batch of 100 beats made through 2019, with the exception of a few beats made between 2016-2018. Laced with audio personally captured in New York City and tags exclaiming "Preservation, Cultivation, Experimentation", "world art, pt. i" embodies black artistry and it's worldliness.
